<Review ID>7544630
<Product Name>iRiver CXW-2G Clix 2 GB Digital Music and Video Player, White
<Title>Nice little player
<Date>Tue Dec 05 00:00:00 CST 2006
<Content>The Clix is easy to use, has a lot of features, and looks and sounds great.  The screen is small but super-clear, and there are three brightness levels to choose from.  Moving music to and from the player is very easy with Windows Media Player 11, which most everyone has already -- no annoying iTunes to deal with.  I don't know of any Apple product that costs under $200 and comes standard with FM radio, voice recording, picture and video capability, and flash games capability.  Plus, this player sounds a lot better than most of the iPods I've listened to, with decent bass from the included earbuds.  The four-sided click-screen could stand to feel a little more sturdy, but I haven't felt concerned about breaking mine at all.  I have to use the locking switch more than I would like to, though, because it's a pretty light touch to click the screen, especially when slipping the player into its included protective sleeve.  A nice touch is the little wiping pad that's attached to the sleeve for cleaning finger smudges off the screen.  The flash games (available from the iRiver web site) are great for keeping you busy when you're tired of music, my favorites being free cell, sudoku, and blackjack -- the cartooney games are disappointingly boring and simplistic.  Pros:  Slick package, unique interface, great features, easy to use, nice sound, acceptable battery charge.  Cons:  Could be built of sturdier stuff like an iPod.  Only available with 2GB memory (about 450-500 songs) -- if that's enough for you, then it's all gravy.  If you absolutely must have every song on your player, spend two to three times as much cash on another product that may or may not include the Clix's standard features.  
<Overall>4

